{"id":13,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":13,"title":"Chapter 10: Jacob and Sherem","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 10"],["h1","Jacob and Sherem"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p3"},"Before Nephi died he gave the plates he had written on to his younger brother Jacob. Jacob was righteous."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/1.1-2,8"},"Jacob 1:1–2, 8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p5"},"Nephi told Jacob to write the things that would help the people believe in Jesus Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/1.4-6"},"Jacob 1:4–6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p7"},"Nephi gave Jacob the power to be a priest in the Church and to teach the Nephites the word of God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/1.18"},"Jacob 1:18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p9"},"After Nephi died many of the Nephites became wicked. Jacob taught the people and told them to repent of the bad things they were doing."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/1.15-17"},"Jacob 1:15–17"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p11"},"A wicked man named Sherem went among the Nephites, teaching them not to believe in Jesus Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.1-2"},"Jacob 7:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p13"},"Sherem told the people that there would be no Christ. Many people believed Sherem."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.2-3"},"Jacob 7:2–3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p15"},"Jacob taught the people to believe in Christ. Sherem wanted to argue with Jacob and persuade him that there would be no Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.6"},"Jacob 7:6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p17"},"Jacob’s faith in Jesus Christ could not be shaken. He had seen angels and had heard the Lord’s voice. He knew Jesus would come."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.5"},"Jacob 7:5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p19"},"The Holy Ghost was with Jacob as he bore his testimony of Jesus Christ to Sherem."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.8-12"},"Jacob 7:8–12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p21"},"Sherem asked to see a sign. He wanted Jacob to prove there is a God. He wanted to see a miracle."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.13"},"Jacob 7:13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p23"},"Jacob would not ask God for a sign. He said Sherem already knew that what Jacob had taught was true."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.14"},"Jacob 7:14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p25"},"Jacob said if God struck Sherem, that would be a sign of God’s power."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.14"},"Jacob 7:14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p27"},"Sherem immediately fell down. He could not get up for many days."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.15"},"Jacob 7:15"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p29"},"Sherem was weak and knew he was going to die. He called the people together."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.16"},"Jacob 7:16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p31"},"He told them he had lied. He said they should believe in Jesus Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.17-19"},"Jacob 7:17–19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p33"},"After Sherem finished talking to the people, he died. The people felt God’s power, and they fell to the ground."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.20-21"},"Jacob 7:20–21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_013_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p35"},"The people began to repent and read the scriptures. They lived in peace and love. Jacob was happy and knew that God had answered his prayers."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-10-jacob-and-sherem.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.22-23"},"Jacob 7:22–23"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
